description: Flatwhite is an AOP library with MVC and WebAPI ActionFilter style using Castle dynamic proxy. You can create MethodFilterAttribute to add custom logic to any methods as soon as it is interceptable by Castle Dynamic Proxy. Flatwhite has 1 built-in OutputCacheFilter to cache method result which can auto refresh stale content. You can use Flatwhite simply for caching or extending behavior of your methods such as profiling, logging by implement MethodFilterAttribute similar to MVC's ActionFilterAttribute

description: Flatwhite.WebApi is an high performance output cache library for WebApi with VaryByParam (on action method) and VaryByHeader support, facilitate usages of cache control and HTTP Cache-Control Extensions for Stale Content. It auto refreshes the stale content so the action method call will never wait. It intercepts the request at the earliest stage to see if cache data is available and return 304 if applicable. So most of the case, the WebAPI engine doesn't need to create API controllers and other stuff which boost the performance to the limit.

Flatwhite is an AOP library with MVC and WebAPI ActionFilter style using Castle dynamic proxy. You can create MethodFilterAttribute to add custom logic to any methods as soon as it is interceptable by Castle Dynamic Proxy. Flatwhite has 1 built-in OutputCacheFilter to cache method result which can auto refresh stale content. You can use Flatwhite simply for caching or extending behavior of your methods such as profiling, logging by implement MethodFilterAttribute similar to MVC's ActionFilterAttribute. Flatwhite.Autofac is a Autofac support package for Flatwhite core

description: Flatwhite.WebApi is an high performance output cache library for WebApi with VaryByParam (on action method) and VaryByHeader support, facilitate usages of cache control and HTTP Cache-Control Extensions for Stale Content. It auto refreshes the stale content so the action method call will never wait. It intercepts the request at the earliest stage to see if cache data is available and return 304 if applicable. So most of the case, the WebAPI engine doesn't need to create API controllers and other stuff which boost the performance to the limit.

description:
West Wind Globalization provides custom data driven .NET ResourceManagers and ResourceProviders for both plain .NET and ASP.NET applications as well as serving JavaScript resources from .NET resources. There's also a a rich real time Web Resource editor that can update resources live but you'll need the Web NuGet package for that feature to light up. 

This core package includes only core, non-Web specific features which include the custom ResourceManager implementation with support for SQL Server, Sql Server Compact, MySql  and SqLite, DbRes dynamic resource access, DbResxConverter and strongly typed class generator. All the 'core' system features are contained in this package. 

If you want to use ASP.NET ResourceProviders, JavaScript resources from .NET Resources, or the Web Resource Editor add the Westwind.Globalization.Web package.
Library of functions used by software applications that automate tasks in the Proteomics Research Information and Management System (PRISM) at Pacific Northwest National Laboratory.
Chrome binding library for Bridge.NET projects.

This library provides the ASP.NET Core specific components to the Westwind.Globalization library. It contains an database ILocalizer interface, JavaScript Resource handler and  the on-line Resource editor to allow editing of data resources in real time.  

 Note: In order to use the Localization Administration feature, please download the required project resources from: https://github.com/RickStrahl/Westwind.Globalization/blob/master/DownloadableAssets/LocalizationAdministrationHtml_AspNetCore.zip

This library is required for using Westwind.Globalization in most ASP.NET Web Projects. MVC Projects that don't require the Web Resource Editor interface, can use just the Core package.
